,"1190":"1190","Abt 1260":"about 1260","1210":"1210","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Abt 1190":"about 1190","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cameron","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish:","in the Highlands, it is usually a nickname from Gaelic <i>cam</i> ‘crooked, bent’ + <i>sròn</i> ‘nose’.","in the Lowlands it is also a habitational name from any of various places called Cameron, especially in Fife."],"variants":[{"name":"Camren","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Cameron  ."]},{"name":"Cambron","meanings":["Spanish (<b>Cambrón</b>): habitational name from any of several places in the provinces of Cáceres and Murcia called Cambrón.","Scottish: altered form of   Cameron  .","French: habitational name from any of the places in Somme and Aisne called Cambron. Alternatively, from a diminutive of <i>c(h)ambre</i> ‘room’ (see   Cambre  )."]},{"name":"Camron","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Cameron  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Cameron was born about 1190, in Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died about 1260, in his hometown, at the age of 72."},"et":{"Abt 1190–Abt 1260":"umbes 1190–umbes 1260","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190–1260":"1190–1260","1190":"1190","Abt 1260":"umbes 1260","1210":"1210","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Abt 1190":"umbes 1190","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1190–Abt 1260":"noin 1190–noin 1260","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190–1260":"1190–1260","1190":"1190","Abt 1260":"noin 1260","1210":"1210","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Abt 1190":"noin 1190","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1190–Abt 1260":"environ 1190–environ 1260","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190–1260":"1190–1260","1190":"1190","Abt 1260":"environ 1260","1210":"1210","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Abt 1190":"environ 1190","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Cameron est né environ 1190, à Perthshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé environ 1260, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 72 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1190–Abt 1260":"um 1190–um 1260","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190–1260":"1190–1260","1190":"1190","Abt 1260":"um 1260","1210":"1210","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Abt 1190":"um 1190","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert Cameron wurde um 1190 in Perthshire, Schottland, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb um 1260 im Alter von 72 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"Abt 1190–Abt 1260":"about 1190–about 1260","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190–1260":"1190–1260","1190":"1190","Abt 1260":"about 1260","1210":"1210","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Abt 1190":"about 1190","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Ecosse, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"Abt 1190–Abt 1260":"1190 körül–1260 körül","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190–